Four people were separately charged with defilement and rape in an Eldoret court.
 They are alleged to have committed the offences before and on Christmas Day. 
 ALSO READ:

Talks that exclude electoral injustice are a waste of time

 Kennedy Kipkemei faced two alternative charges of defiling and raping his 12-year-old step-daughter.
 Kipkemei is alleged to have committed the offence on December 25, 2017, at Mti Moja in Eldoret West.




(adsbygoogle = window.adsbygoogle || []).push({});

 Philip Omaya was also charged with defiling a nine-year-old girl on the same day at Imbinga village in Likuyani, Kakamega County.
 The two denied the charges and were released on a bond of Sh200, 000 each by Eldoret Senior Principal Magistrate Harrison Barasa.
 The two cases will be heard on January 8, 2018.
 Another suspect, David Shikoli, was charged with raping a woman on December 23 in Kambi Miwa estate in Eldoret West, Uasin Gishu County.
 Shikoli pleaded not guilty to the charges and was released on a bond of Sh200, 000 with a surety of a similar amount.
 Stephen Musyoka Mwangangi was charged with defiling a 16-year-old girl on different dates between December 10 and 25 in Lusweti village in Eldoret East. 
